text: The 1934 Western Reserve Red Cats football team represented Western Reserve University in the American city of Cleveland, Ohio, now known as Case Western Reserve University, during the 1934 college football season. The team was coached by head coach Sam Willaman, whose coaching staff included assistant coach Bill Edwards. ==Schedule== ==References== Western Reserve Category:Case Western Reserve Spartans football seasons Western Reserve Football
